s=\frac{1-2r +-\sqrt{(2r-1)^2+16p}}{4}
p = 4s \frac{(s - 1)}{2} + s (2r + 1)\\ \implies p = 2s^2-2s  + 2rs +s=2s^2-s(-2+2r+1)\\ \implies 2s^2+s(2-2r-1)-p=0\\ \implies\text{By the quadratic formula, }s=-(2-2r-1)\pm\sqrt{(2-2r-1)^2+8p}\\ \implies \boxed{s=2r-1\pm\sqrt{4r^2-4r+1+8p}}
